How to config LXR on Ubuntu

### 1. install perl
  > sudo apt install perl

### 2. install ctags
  install from respos:
  > sudo apt install exuberant-ctags

  install from source:
  > ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/ctags
  >
  > make && make install
  >
  > vim ~/.bashrc
  >
  > export PATH=/usr/local/ctags/bin:$PATH

### 3. install mysql-server
  > sudo apt install mysql-server

### 4. install lighttpd
  > sudo apt install lighttpd

### 5. install glimse
  > sudo apt install flex (install this firstly)
  >
  > wget http://webglimpse.net/trial/glimpse-latest.tar.gz
  >
  > ./configure
  >
  > make & make install

### 6. install perl modules
  > apt install libdbi-perl
  >
  > apt install libfile-mmagic-perl
  >
  >apt install libdbd-mysql-perl

### 7. install LXR from release version
  > cp LXR /home/meng/lxr

### 8. configure lxr
  > ./scripts/configure-lxr.pl --v
